Preconditions:
- The input grid is a square grid with dimensions n x n.
- Each value in the grid represents the height of a tower of cubes placed on top of the corresponding cell.
- The values in the grid are non-negative integers.
- The grid contains at least one cell.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the total surface area of the resulting shapes.
- The bottom face of each shape is included in the surface area calculation.
- The resulting shapes are formed by gluing any directly adjacent cubes to each other.
- The resulting shapes are irregular 3D shapes.